Sentencas: A series of iron-based perovskite oxides BaFe1-xCuxO3-delta (x = 0.10, 0.15, 0.20 and 0.25, abbreviated as BFC-10, BFC-15, BFC-20 and BFC-25, respectively) as cathode materials have been prepared via a combined EDTA-citrate complexing sol-gel method.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The effects of Cu contents on the crystal structure, chemical stability, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and electrochemical properties of BFC-x materials have been studied.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: All the BFC-x samples exhibit the cubic phase with a space group Pm3m (221).
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity decreases with increasing Cu content.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The maximum electrical conductivity is 60.9 +/- 0.9 S cm(-1) for BFC-20 at 600 degrees C. Substitution of Fe by Cu increases the thermal expansion coefficient.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The average TEC increases from 20.6.10(-6) K-1 for BFC-10 to 23.7.10-6 K-1 for BFC-25 at the temperature range of 30-850 degrees C. Among the samples, BFC-20 shows the best electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of BFC-20 on SDC electrolyte is 0.014 W cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The single fuel cell with the configguration of BFC-20/SDC/NiO-SDC delivers the highest power density of 0.57 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode

Sentencas: The favorable electrochemical activities can be attributed to the cubic lattice structure and the high oxygen vacancy concentration caused by Cu doping.
Titulo: Synthesis and Electrochemical Properties of BaFe1-xCuxO3-δ Perovskite Oxide for IT-SOFC Cathode
